$ Linux kernel module

A (loadable) kernel module extends the functionality of the →Linux/kernel[kernel] (new →hardware, →Linux/filesystem, system calls) or modifies the behavior of the kernel.

Modules can be loaded/unloaded without restarting the kernel.

{ Parameters

  When loaded into the kernel, a module shows its parameters in → Linux/fhs/sys/module/module-name/parameter/parameter-name.

}

{ Module names

  Hyphens (`-`) and underscores (`_`) are not differentiated in module names.

}

{ See also

  → Linux/shell/commands/modinfo

}
